  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      IBD-related arthropathy is one of a group of inflammatory arthritides considered as
      seronegative spondyloarthropathies, a group of disorders that also includes ankylosing
      spondylitis, psoriatic arthritis, reactive arthritis, and undifferentiated SpA. IBD-related
      SpA is mainly characterized by axial involvement but may also be associated with peripheral
      symptoms, such as synovitis, dactylitis, or enthesitis
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
